A dry breeze blew gently in the afternoon. The man selling miscellaneous items at a street vendor thought he had a rare customer. [l][r]
A young woman of Asian appearance asking haltingly what lies ahead on the road [r]
There were two European-looking women asking about the items for sale in broken Japanese. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
[r]"There's a town up ahead. However, like the rest of the country, it hasn't completely escaped the chaos of the civil war. I don't think it's the right place for two young girls like you to go."[l][r]
The shopkeeper advises him, but it doesn't seem to make sense.
It was unclear whether she was there or not. The black-haired woman muttered a short thank you and stared straight ahead down the road. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
At that moment, another blonde woman let out a cheer, her blue eyes shining. She held up one of the items for sale in both hands and made gestures to ask to have it sold to her. [l][r]
His companions seem to be trying to stop him, but those bright blue eyes show no intention of listening.[l][r]
The shopkeeper is, of course, a businessman. If someone wants to buy, he wants to sell. [l][r]
[r] In truth, he wanted to ask for a higher price, but he decided that he should get the deal done quickly and not let his black-haired companion get in the way, so he raised his finger and told him the going rate. [l][r]
Hekigan seemed to be satisfied with the price. [l] He paid with a smile and left the store with the antique item in his arms, to the complaints of his partner. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
The item was roughly dusted off and gently placed on top of the blonde.[l][r]
Short brim steel Brody helmet[r]
It was the same one the black-haired girl was wearing in the apocalyptic city. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

