"Yay, now I can become Chi-chan too! In other words, I'm a god!"[l][r]
"If that's how you can become me, then how cheap of a god must you be?" [l][r]
"God is God, no matter how cheap or small." [l][r]
"Then the dinner you lost for that helmet[r]
Give me your money, my dear." [l][r]
"He's a low-ranking god, so I don't like him." [l][r]
"Give you the word incoherent
It's a gift from God, be happy." [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
As they were talking to each other, an old man was watching over them from the window of a house they passed.[l][r]
[r]Squinting from under his square-rimmed glasses, the old man watched them leave until their backs were out of sight. [l][r]
[r]With a gentle smile on his face, filled with nostalgia and affection. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

